---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
const cover = "/bermuda-cover.svg";
const PRODUCT = "https://www.chrisstirling.com/product-page/crimson-cross-the-bermuda-years-working-title";
---
<Base title="Crimson Cross: The Bermuda Years | Chris Stirling" description="The prequel novella to the Crimson Cross series — Thomas Drayton's Bermuda years.">
  <main class="wrap">
    <section class="pad" style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:420px 1fr;gap:50px;align-items:start;padding-top:48px;">
      <div>
        <img src={cover} alt="Crimson Cross: The Bermuda Years cover" style="width:420px;max-width:100%;border-radius:8px;box-shadow:0 18px 44px rgba(20,40,55,.22);display:block;" />
        <div style="margin-top:18px;">
          <a class="btn btn-crimson" href={PRODUCT}>More info · $14.99</a>
        </div>
        <p style="color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;margin-top:10px;">Prequel novella</p>
      </div>
      <div class="prose">
        <div class="eyebrow">Prequel · The Crimson Cross series</div>
        <h1>Crimson Cross: The Bermuda Years</h1>
        <p>Before the Azure Waves, there was Bermuda. This prequel novella takes readers to the sun-bleached coral fortress where Thomas Drayton first earned his reputation — as both a brilliant military tactician and a devoted family man.</p>
        <p>As commander of Bermuda's defenses, Thomas builds the life and the name his son Samuel will one day fight to avenge. It's the calm, sunled chapter before the storm of <em>Azure Waves</em> — essential reading for anyone who wants to understand how the conspiracy began, and what was truly lost when Charleston burned.</p>
        <div class="card" style="margin-top:24px;max-width:520px;">
          <h3>Start the saga</h3>
          <p style="font-size:15px;margin:6px 0 12px;">New to Crimson Cross? Begin with Book One.</p>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost btn-sm" href="/books/azure-waves">Crimson Cross: Azure Waves</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>
